Key Match Events: Scottie Barnes recorded a triple-double with 33 points, 13 rebounds, and 5 assists
Immanuel Quickley added 21 points and 15 assists
Gradey Dick had 22 points and 3 steals
Jakob Poeltl amassed 12 points and 9 rebounds
D’Angelo Russell scored 22 points off the bench
Nic Claxton had 16 points and 10 rebounds
Post-Match Reflections: Scottie Barnes expressed pride in his team's performance after the win
Immanuel Quickley emphasized the importance of strong perimeter defense
Miscellaneous Highlights: Toronto shot 55.1 percent (27-for-49) from the field in the first half, and Brooklyn shot 50 percent (23-for-46)
The Raptors ended an 11-game losing streak
Noah Clowney fell on his back going for a rebound and went to the dressing room with 26 seconds left in the third quarter
Maxwell Lewis was helped off the court and taken to the dressing room after falling late in the fourth quarter
RJ Barrett (illness), Bruce Brown (knee), and Cam Thomas (hamstring) did not play
